Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:02.52,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.52,0:00:03.72,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.52,0:00:07.27,sign_61_4_Comprehensive_Su,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Comprehensive Summer Training Documents
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.72,0:00:05.25,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.57,0:00:07.97,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,That's what goes through my mind, \Nevery day, after I confirm it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.97,0:00:11.44,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,At school, at home, at my job,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.11,0:00:11.44,sign_243_8_Ray_of_Hope_For_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Ray of Hope For Civilian Antarctic Expedition?\NShichishin-ya to Sign Contract to Sponsor "Challenge For Antarctic"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:12.57,note,sign,0000,0000,0000,,We got some tickets for this,\Nso if you're interested,\Ncome see management.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:13.86,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I say it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.94,0:00:16.75,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to Antarctica!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:21.33,Main,stu,0000,0000,0000,,She actually said Antarctica!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.01,0:00:23.81,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You don't care?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.81,0:00:24.33,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.96,0:00:27.33,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as if they'd believe \Nme right now anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.85,0:00:29.59,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say it after I've really gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:33.84,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,"In your face, in your face, in your face!"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:37.38,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You're kind of a jerk, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.38,0:00:38.55,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.91,0:00:40.01,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,You mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.01,0:00:40.87,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.65,0:00:59.20,Show_Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2280,1225)}A Place Further Than the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:21.49,Ep_Title,title,0000,0000,0000,,Fo{\c&HAC8B52&}ur {\c&H966882&}Ca{\c&H6F6FE0&}ter{\c&H44ABBA&}pi{\c&H49D258&}ll{\c&H8B59EC&}ars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:21.49,Likes/Comments,sign,0000,0000,0000,,5 Likes\N4 Comments
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:21.49,Hashtags,sign,0000,0000,0000,,#ShutUp #InYourFace #Compasser
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:23.99,sign_3393_25_Always_check_the,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Always check the lower door before \Nand after closing the freezer door
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.07,0:02:23.99,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,You're serious about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.34,0:02:27.28,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,You need two days off for \Nthis "summer training,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:30.81,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,and then you'll be taking time \Noff beginning in December?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:31.60,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.60,0:02:33.13,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,What do your parents have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.13,0:02:34.67,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,We have their permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.00,0:02:35.75,sign_3693_32_I_hereby_grant_p,sign,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby grant permission as guardian of your student\N(Kobuchizawa Shirase) for them to take the following time off:\N(Student's Class) Year 2 Class 2 \N(Student Name) Kobuchizawa Shirase\N(Guardian Name) Kobuchizawa Koumi\NTo join the Civilian Antarctic Expedition \N"Challenge For Antarctic" team and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.71,0:02:38.34,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:41.53,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.61,0:02:48.48,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Rin?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.48,0:02:49.77,Main,rin,0000,0000,0000,,Seems pretty normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:52.08,Main,rin,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't slam the refrigerator door,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.08,0:02:54.73,Main,rin,0000,0000,0000,,and the rhythm of her \Nchopping seems normal...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.70,0:02:56.57,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.94,0:02:57.48,Main,rin,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.17,0:03:00.67,Main,rin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm suspicious. It's {\i1}too{\i0} normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.67,0:03:03.57,Main,rin,0000,0000,0000,,Like it's all a front, to trick us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.13,0:03:04.91,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Mari-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.92,0:03:07.83,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.18,0:03:11.33,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,I bought some bath salts. \NCould you take them to the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.85,0:03:13.83,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:22.72,sign_4825_47_Feels_Like_Antar,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Feels Like Antarctica
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:22.72,sign_4825_48_Medicinal_Bath_S,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Medicinal\NBath Salts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:22.72,sign_4825_49_Mint,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Mint
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:22.72,sign_4825_50_Limited_Time,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Limited Time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.16,0:03:27.10,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,They started selling those recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.63,0:03:30.10,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Does she already know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.41,0:03:33.12,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,No, it might just be a coincidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:35.22,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,If I jump to conclusions, \NI might be digging my own grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.22,0:03:37.21,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But what if she knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.97,0:03:42.43,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,If she does, then trying to hide \Nit might make the situation worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.43,0:03:43.99,Italics,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I should be just come clean, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:45.16,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Mari-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:46.80,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.80,0:03:49.29,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Or is there something on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.04,0:03:53.33,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Antarctica, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.09,0:03:59.63,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.63,0:04:02.97,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I've decided \Nto take a trip this winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.74,0:04:05.39,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's a done deal, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.53,0:04:08.80,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,I simply hadn't heard a {\i1}thing{\i0} about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.80,0:04:10.77,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Not until a neighbor told me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:12.08,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh, was {\i1}I{\i0} embarrassed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.63,0:04:14.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, I meant to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.77,0:04:19.23,sign_6109_70_I_hereby_grant_p,sign,0000,0000,0000,,I hereby grant permission as guardian of your student\N(Tamaki Mari) for them to take the following time off:\N(Student's Class) Year 2 Class 3 \N(Student Name) Tamaki Mari\N(Guardian Name) Tamaki Yoko\NTo join the Civilian Antarctic Expedition \N"Challenge For Antarctic" team...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.03,0:04:19.23,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It was just an issue of t-t-timing, \Nand we needed to be sure it was happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.23,0:04:20.65,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Who filled this in, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.40,0:04:23.74,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,And who stamped it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.07,0:04:28.83,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait, wait, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:31.60,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,At least put down the weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.60,0:04:34.34,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a weapon. It's a cooking utensil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:37.88,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Though I could use it to dish out {\i1}something{\i0} \Nto a certain idiot daughter of mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.88,0:04:40.06,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,That's a terrifying thing to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.06,0:04:40.94,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ho—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.94,0:04:42.27,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:50.62,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.69,0:04:51.27,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.27,0:04:54.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Da—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.77,0:04:58.52,sign_7068_83_Social_Studies_T,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Social Studies\NTerminology
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.93,0:04:58.52,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,This is pretty much all on you, Kimari.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.85,0:05:01.19,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to sum it all up like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.19,0:05:04.29,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can't go unless I pass every single test!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:07.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,And even without that, I won't have any \Ntime to study during our training camp...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.77,0:05:10.03,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,You're really taking time \Noff next week, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.03,0:05:13.78,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's four days, including the weekend, \Nso I'll be off through Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.78,0:05:16.04,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:19.20,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,I read that they're not even sure \Nif the boat will leave the harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.20,0:05:22.50,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not like I can \Ndo anything about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.92,0:05:24.27,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta get to my job!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:25.38,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,Rough life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:26.86,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:28.26,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,Don't overwork yourself, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.27,0:05:34.77,Main,meg,0000,0000,0000,,If you work too hard and it doesn't go \Nthrough, you're really going to regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.61,0:05:39.27,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Right. See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:49.16,sign_8315_99_Standardized_Tes,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Standardized Test Guide\N{\c&H4759C8&}High School 2\N{\c&H3A4849&}English
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.12,0:05:49.16,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I request your assistance!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:49.72,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,No dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.72,0:05:50.60,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.60,0:05:54.54,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Look, going to school means \Nyou're taking classes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.05,0:06:00.18,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,That means you've got tons of time \Nallotted every day just for learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.59,0:06:04.24,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,If you still can't do it, you're probably \Njust not putting in the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.24,0:06:09.05,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Academics aren't like sports. \NAnyone can pick this stuff up if they try.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:09.92,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:10.68,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.68,0:06:12.31,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.31,0:06:14.72,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Hinata's right, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.64,0:06:18.40,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, whatever. I'll ask Yuzuki-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.40,0:06:19.69,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,She's younger than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:21.31,sign_9109_113_I_m_outside_the_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,I'm outside the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:22.72,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,She's here, she says!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:28.98,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.98,0:06:30.45,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You seem different today...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.88,0:06:33.60,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I was at work last time. \NI had to dress that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.60,0:06:34.88,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You had to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:38.10,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I just look awful in that \Ncutesy stuff, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.10,0:06:40.31,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,It's really not "me."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:41.16,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.16,0:06:43.09,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you looked cute...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.47,0:06:47.70,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand that "Look at \Nme, I'm a girly-girl!" junk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.78,0:06:50.84,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Why's she in such a bad mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:53.99,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Well, her job being what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.99,0:06:55.70,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,she probably deals with \Nsome complicated stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.86,0:07:00.85,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.09,0:07:03.70,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.65,0:07:10.36,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.68,0:07:13.24,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry that it wasn't\Nthe easiest place to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:14.62,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.54,0:07:18.12,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry, I'll tidy it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.12,0:07:19.50,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:31.71,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't quite what I was expecting...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.99,0:07:34.77,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Not quite what you were expecting, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.06,0:07:37.71,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess it wouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.71,0:07:41.56,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,An Antarctic expedition \Nis a very big project.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.56,0:07:45.19,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we are civilians, you wouldn't \Nexpect a junky old minivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.40,0:07:48.94,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,How are we supposed to respond to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.94,0:07:49.44,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'd know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.87,0:07:56.28,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,But I never thought you'd manage \Nto end up coming with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.58,0:07:58.34,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to your million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.34,0:07:59.75,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I still have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.28,0:08:01.87,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need it, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:05.88,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,As I'm sure you've read, \Nwe don't have any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.88,0:08:12.88,sign_11650_146_Do_not_insert_ta,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Do not\Ninsert tape!\NDANGER!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.27,0:08:10.15,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,So we're doing a whole lot to raise \Nthe funds to get to Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.15,0:08:14.16,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,That also means we're trimming \Nevery bit of fat that we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:17.47,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We won't let it be canceled. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.47,0:08:22.35,sign_11928_150_Civilian_Japanes,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,140)}Civilian Japanese Antarctic Expedition\N"Challenge for Antarctic (2nd)"\NSponsor Recruitment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.09,0:08:20.22,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,You girls might not know this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:24.48,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,but we've been hearing the same thing \Nover and over since the project started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.56,0:08:24.48,sign_12050_153_Icebreaker_Shria,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Icebreaker Shirase\N{\c&HA1AFA3&}Recruiting naming\Nrights partners!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.56,0:08:24.48,sign_12050_154_Your_name_here_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Your name here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.56,0:08:24.48,sign_12050_155_Pins,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Pins
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:27.81,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,"You don't have the money. \NWon't it be dangerous?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.24,0:08:29.40,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We're used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:30.99,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,You are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.25,0:08:33.05,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Any time one of those reports comes out,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.05,0:08:35.36,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,the rest of the team and I \Nall shout together...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.89,0:08:39.05,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,"Shut up, idiots!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.94,0:08:41.70,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.47,0:08:45.46,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,We do that, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.35,0:08:47.33,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:48.19,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.86,0:08:55.34,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,The mountains, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.29,0:08:57.79,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Feels nice out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.78,0:08:59.35,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Though we won't be going out \Nthere until two days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:03.35,sign_12932_169_Hundred_Mountain,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Hundred Mountains Lodge\N{\fs12}Altitude [3026M]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:01.71,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Today and tomorrow, it's all lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.71,0:09:03.35,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.41,0:09:07.19,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Check these documents!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.55,0:09:09.69,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! A station handbook?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.69,0:09:12.69,sign_13180_174_Internal_Documen,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Internal Documents\NHandle with care
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.69,0:09:12.69,sign_13180_175_Station_Handbook,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Station Handbook
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:12.69,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,"Internal documents... handle with care."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:15.20,sign_13252_179_Syowa_Station,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Syowa Station
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:15.20,sign_13252_180_Construction_of_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Construction of new station
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.99,0:09:15.20,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, a snowcat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:16.85,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,This is so exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:17.45,sign_13312_181_Discovery_of_lar,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Discovery of large numbers of meteorites
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:17.45,sign_13312_182_The_collection_o,sign,0000,0000,0000,,The collection of meteorites across the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:17.45,sign_13312_183_17_100_discovere,sign,0000,0000,0000,,17,100 discovered. The world's largest collection of meteorites.\NAmong them, we've located nine {\c&H363161&}Mars meteorites {\c&H322823&}and nine {\c&H363161&}Moon meteorites{\c&H322823&}.\N(Reference) America: 17,301 China: 9,826 Korea: 21 Other (including Europe): 869
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:17.45,sign_13312_184_Mars_Meteorite,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Mars Meteorite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:17.45,sign_13312_185_How_meteors_accu,sign,0000,0000,0000,,How meteors accumulate in Antarctica
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:22.44,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Based on that documentation,\NI'll be giving you a condensed version
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.44,0:09:27.21,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,of the summer and winter \Ntraining the others get.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.52,0:09:33.96,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Antarctica is the only continent in the \Nworld with no permanent inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:36.20,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_190_Joint_Internatio,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Joint International Expeditions Under the Antarctic Treaty System
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_191_Primary_Base_Dis,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Primary Base Distribution
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_192_Countries_partic,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Countries participating in Antarctic expeditions: 29\NWintering stations: 20
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_192_Ross_Island_Regi,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Ross Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_193_Dome_Fuji,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Dome Fuji
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_194_Mizuho__________,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuho            Asuka
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_195_Queen_Maud_Land_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Maud Land\NAntarctic Treaty System
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_196_Antarctic_Penins,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Antarctic Peninsula
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:40.97,sign_13762_199_Prydz_Bay_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Prydz Bay
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.20,0:09:38.65,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,it has many rules surrounding its use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.65,0:09:40.97,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to be sure to memorize them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.97,0:09:41.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:43.94,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,You're not like this in school...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.22,0:09:45.48,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't in my class!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:48.25,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's meet the team captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.47,0:09:59.82,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I am this Antarctic expedition's \Ncaptain, Todo Gin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.09,0:10:01.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.77,0:10:03.83,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,It's a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.14,0:10:06.08,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to start by saying this:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.08,0:10:10.32,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Whether the members of my team are \Nresearchers or just accompanying us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.32,0:10:12.34,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I will treat you all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:14.86,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,We have many things to accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.86,0:10:19.69,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Just because you're in high school doesn't \Nmean I won't ask you to do everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.69,0:10:21.52,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,from laundry to hard labor, as necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.52,0:10:23.32,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.32,0:10:24.01,Main,all,0000,0000,0000,,Yes ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.01,0:10:28.39,sign_14962_216_The_ABCs_of_Anta,sign,0000,0000,0000,,The ABCs of Antarctic Expedition
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.01,0:10:28.39,sign_14962_217_A__Always_follow,sign,0000,0000,0000,,A: Always follow procedure\NB: Be alert at all times\NC: Common sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:28.39,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,These are the ABCs of \Nan antarctic expedition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.88,0:10:31.02,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,A: Always follow procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.02,0:10:32.90,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,B: Be alert at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.90,0:10:34.90,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,C: Common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.29,0:10:37.44,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to keep these in mind at all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.03,0:10:44.03,sign_15322_223_1__I_want_to_liv,sign,0000,0000,0000,,1. I want to live\N2. I want to know\N3. I want to keep my team together\NAll of these apply on an Antarctic expedition.\NNo matter what, you must survive and come home alive.\NEagerly pursue knowledge and new experiences.\NLastly, never leave a member of your team behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.57,0:10:49.29,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,She sure did sound like a real captain, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.60,0:10:51.88,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,If you dozed off around her, \Nyou'd have chalk coming your way, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:55.17,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,If we had a test, I bet she'd fill \Nit with all the hardest questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.03,0:10:59.55,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,We're surveying a route tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.71,0:11:01.64,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we'll be going outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:04.71,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be a waste not to, being up \Nhere in the mountains and all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:07.98,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Still, this all looks pretty tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.19,0:11:12.31,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.62,0:11:13.80,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,How did what go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.80,0:11:15.60,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing her again after so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:17.43,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.79,0:11:20.35,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to treat her like \Nany other member of the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.35,0:11:21.43,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.00,0:11:27.58,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Did you go against my wishes on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.93,0:11:30.46,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't have any part of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.08,0:11:35.10,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,That girl really got here \Nthrough her own efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.10,0:11:37.84,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Though I must admit, \NI had a feeling she would...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.42,0:11:43.12,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Since the first day she told \Nme she wanted to come along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.95,0:11:47.60,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,She's Takako's daughter, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:54.06,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.06,0:11:56.23,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,A transceiver, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.56,0:12:00.61,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a compass, and that's a GPS...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:02.29,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,And then we've got flags.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:04.21,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Hinata-chan, do you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:06.12,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she taught us most \Nof it to us yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:08.83,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But why do we have to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.83,0:12:10.50,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Antarctica's flat, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.87,0:12:13.46,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,We can get along fine without \Nmarking a route, can't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.46,0:12:14.56,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Totally wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:16.53,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,The landscape's white as far as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.53,0:12:18.88,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,so it's easy lose track of \Nyour direction in a blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.65,0:12:23.38,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you need to create \Na route to walk along.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.94,0:12:26.93,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,So we set up the flags to \Nserve as landmarks, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.93,0:12:28.19,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But where do we put them?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.19,0:12:31.14,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Figuring that out is the \Npoint of the training.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:34.69,sign_18010_260_Communication_st,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,600,)}Communication station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:34.69,sign_18010_261_Route_Creation_S,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,600,)}Route Creation Start Point
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.57,0:12:33.97,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,This is our current location.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.97,0:12:36.43,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,And this is our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.64,0:12:41.15,sign_18094_262_Route_Creation_E,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(656,1)}Route Creation End Point
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.64,0:12:41.15,sign_18094_263_Route_Creation_C,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(656,1)}Route Creation Course
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.43,0:12:38.20,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,So we just have to get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:39.64,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't just go right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.64,0:12:42.70,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,We have to go here, here, \Nand here on the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.70,0:12:45.01,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,and set up flags at each point.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:46.57,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.83,0:12:47.99,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.99,0:12:49.12,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,That way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.12,0:12:50.14,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.14,0:12:52.31,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just run off willy-nilly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.31,0:12:54.64,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even know where the points are?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.59,0:12:58.46,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,There... ish?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.68,0:13:00.46,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,"Ish"? Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.37,0:13:04.16,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to keep precise \Ntrack of our location.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:11.89,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting the feeling \Nthis is gonna be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.34,0:13:16.08,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Forty-eight, forty-nine, fifty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.87,0:13:19.43,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.43,0:13:20.57,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Check the angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.71,0:13:30.58,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Which should I look with? \NLeft eye or right eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.17,0:13:32.70,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Your dominant eye, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.70,0:13:34.01,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Which eye is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.01,0:13:35.80,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I think you go like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.80,0:13:37.08,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done yet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:40.34,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,168 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.56,0:13:43.84,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,More to the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:45.20,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:46.30,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.30,0:13:47.16,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.16,0:13:48.34,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.51,0:13:53.35,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.88,0:14:01.00,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, the latitude is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.00,0:14:02.49,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,And the longitude is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.45,0:14:06.27,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,It seems further away than \Nthe last one, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.27,0:14:10.37,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,If the instruments are right, \Nwe should be right here, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:13.62,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,That's where they are, huh? \NThey've gotten pretty off-track...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:18.72,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,This reminds me of the first time \NI took part in one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:20.74,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,What's the story on the other three?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.74,0:14:25.47,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the one is the girl we were supposed \Nto bring along from the start, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.47,0:14:28.80,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,They seem to have become \Nfriends at some point, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.80,0:14:29.46,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.94,0:14:37.51,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,She said the other expedition members \Nwould compete on time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.51,0:14:41.76,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I think precision is more \Nimportant than speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.76,0:14:43.52,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Safety first, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.25,0:14:45.33,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.75,0:14:48.78,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:53.39,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,398, 399, 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.13,0:14:57.74,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.06,0:15:00.39,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Two steps left!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:04.01,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:06.36,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,That was fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.77,0:15:08.42,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed you could tell, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:10.81,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Kimari must be good with the compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.81,0:15:12.49,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,She does seem cut out for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.49,0:15:14.65,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Just call me a compass expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.65,0:15:16.39,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,A compasser, for short!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.79,Main,all,0000,0000,0000,,First comes rock! Rock-paper-scissors!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:25.15,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll take this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.46,0:15:27.52,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Feels like we're on a field trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.52,0:15:28.80,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone bring any playing cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.80,0:15:30.58,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,We're not here to play around!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:33.44,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping in a tent will \Nbe good training, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.44,0:15:35.64,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not even 8:00 yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.64,0:15:40.16,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, the captain said they'd always \Nsocialize at night during their training camps...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.55,0:15:43.74,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Less talk, more sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:01.17,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.17,0:16:02.22,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.22,0:16:03.31,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna tell scary stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.82,0:16:05.06,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I could just kill you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.80,0:16:08.44,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzuki-chan, do you not like scary stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.82,0:16:10.19,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Please shut talking now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.58,0:16:29.95,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What does "shut talking now" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.95,0:16:32.85,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,You're my senpai, so I self-corrected!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.85,0:16:35.76,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,You knew what I meant, \Nso please leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.76,0:16:37.39,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Please shut talking now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:39.45,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off, Kimari!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.04,0:16:49.10,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Shirase-chan, are you asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.08,0:16:52.03,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering about something...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.03,0:16:56.03,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know the captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.15,0:16:58.21,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,How could you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:16:59.81,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Just had a feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.16,0:17:14.71,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,She and my mother knew \Neach other in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.84,0:17:18.05,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,She went to Antarctica with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:21.87,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,She came home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:25.06,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,My mother didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:26.90,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.93,0:17:34.57,Flashback,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Because... my mother is waiting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.68,0:17:51.88,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What a big sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:52.96,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the North Star?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:57.20,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, were supposed to trace something \Nfrom the Big Dipper, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.20,0:17:58.47,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was Cassiopeia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.82,0:18:00.28,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What's the South Star?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.28,0:18:02.54,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,South Star? Is there one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.54,0:18:06.48,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,There is, but you can't see \Nit as clearly, I've heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.93,0:18:07.79,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Which is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.79,0:18:09.48,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,You can't see it from here, duh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.12,0:18:12.48,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,"Never think the stars you see \Nare all the stars there are."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.94,0:18:14.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Another of your sayings, Hinata-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.77,0:18:16.49,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that one kinda sucked, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.80,0:18:20.37,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,This is Syowa Station. \NAurora Team, do you read me? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.37,0:18:21.56,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,We got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.56,0:18:23.59,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,This is Aurora Team, Miyake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:25.33,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,We read you loud and clear. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.09,0:18:27.48,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,This is your regular check-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.48,0:18:29.67,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Is everything all right there? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.67,0:18:31.61,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Four members of Aurora Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:34.72,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,All personnel and equipment \Naccounted for. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.72,0:18:35.98,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.98,0:18:38.98,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,It gets cold around dawn, so \Nwatch your body temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.98,0:18:40.56,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,This concludes your regular check-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.56,0:18:41.59,Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.99,0:18:43.16,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Be safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.96,0:18:45.12,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,She really did contact us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.12,0:18:47.47,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I almost forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:57.70,sign_27186_377_New_Message,sign,0000,0000,0000,,New Message
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:57.70,sign_27186_377_To__Mom,sign,0000,0000,0000,,To: {\c&H352A28&}Mom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:57.70,sign_27186_378_Subj__Dear_Mom,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Subj: {\c&H302623&}Dear Mom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:18:58.86,sign_27186_377_New_Message,,0000,0000,0000,,Mailbox
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:18:58.86,sign_27278_381_Receipt,,0000,0000,0000,,Receipt
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:18:58.86,sign_27278_382_Favorites,,0000,0000,0000,,Favorites
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.51,0:19:16.19,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,So cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:37.90,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.76,0:19:41.42,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.79,0:20:01.56,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What was Shirase-chan's mom like?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.56,0:20:06.35,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,All I can say about her is \Nthat she was very strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.71,0:20:08.91,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Was she like Shirase-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.91,0:20:12.95,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. I don't know \Nher daughter very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.32,0:20:17.22,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,But in stubbornness and conviction, \Nshe's her spitting image.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.22,0:20:18.23,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,She's trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.80,0:20:21.46,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't trouble just the best?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:24.91,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,A personality like yours \Nwill do well in Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.91,0:20:25.74,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.98,0:20:28.50,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want to go to Antarctica?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.07,0:20:30.67,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Did she invite you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.67,0:20:31.66,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.48,0:20:34.75,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm the one who made the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.17,0:20:37.18,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,That I wanted to go with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.18,0:20:40.26,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,That I didn't want my high school \Nyears to end the way they were going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.87,0:20:43.50,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,That I wanted to go \Nsomewhere that's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.14,0:20:44.76,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.76,0:20:49.05,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But then I met Hinata-chan and Yuzuki-chan,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.05,0:20:51.70,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,and I got to hear how the \Nmembers of the expedition felt,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.70,0:20:54.77,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,and I learned stuff about you \Nand Shirase-chan, and now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.96,0:20:57.46,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just "somewhere" to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.17,0:20:59.73,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,It's Antarctica!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.51,0:21:07.32,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go to Antarctica with all of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.70,0:21:13.17,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.17,0:21:14.17,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.98,0:21:16.93,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a morning person...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.93,0:21:19.04,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Just get up already! \NYou, too, Shirase-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.04,0:21:20.53,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.91,0:21:37.38,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna go with all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.68,0:21:39.90,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna find the South Star with all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.25,0:21:42.90,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna see auroras, eat shaved ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.90,0:21:45.29,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,and take pictures with penguins!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.95,0:21:49.24,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,We've got to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:55.06,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.01,0:23:38.02,sign_33927_420_Kimari,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kimari
